0P00000OZH.F.summary:
The fund is an international pension fund, whose investment policy is geared to achieve a higher return than domestic government bonds, by purchasing higher-yielding bonds with the involvement of foreign currencies.
Focus of the current investment policy of the fund are the bond markets of the countries, which benefit from the European integration process (particularly with regard to later participation on the EWWU).

AT0000740659.VI.summary: The Raiffeisen EuroVision Bond invests in government bonds of the next central and eastern European candidates for EU membership, and in bonds issued by supranational organizations. The falling interest rate levels in the course of alignment to the EU's.
